<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>With current version of ZF (1.10.2), it is very hard (not to say impossible) to make Zend_Rest_Client use a result class other than Zend_Rest_Client_Result.</p>

<p>In my case, I only need to customize Zend_Rest_Client_Result =&gt; I subclass it, but I am not able to make Zend_Rest_Client use this class.</p>

<p>It would be a great increase in flexibility if result-classname was no longer hardcoded, for example storing name of result-class into a property of Zend_Rest_Client so that it could be easily changed.</p>

<p>Culprit seems to be this line (from Zend_Rest_Client.php):</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
    public function __call($method, $args)
    {
        [...]
        return new Zend_Rest_Client_Result($response-&gt;getBody());
    }
</code></pre>

